# 🎨 Tailwind CSS AI Ruleset

## 📌 Best Practices
- **Use Tailwind’s utility classes for styling; avoid inline styles or separate CSS files.**
- **Avoid deep nesting in CSS—use Tailwind’s built-in classes for clarity.**
- **Use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) instead of media queries.**
- **Ensure Tailwind classes are not duplicated unnecessarily.**
- **Enable PurgeCSS to remove unused styles in production.**

## 📐 Layout & Design
- **Use `flex` and `grid` utilities instead of custom layouts.**
- **Prefer `gap-*` for spacing over `margin` when using flex/grid.**
- **Use Tailwind’s `theme()` function in `tailwind.config.js` for reusable styles.**
